1.2 Gaussian Process Regression

set.seed(rand_seed)
n_train <- 20
X <- runif(n_train, min = -7, max = 7)
X_test <- seq(-7,7,length.out=100)
set.seed(rand_seed)
y <- gaussian_process(X=X)
gp_reg <- gaussian_process_regression(X=X, y=y, X_test = X_test)
plot(gp_reg)

set.seed(rand_seed)
length_scale <- 0.3
signal_sd <- 1.08
noise_sd <- 0.00005
y <- gaussian_process(
  X=X, 
  signal_sd=signal_sd, 
  length_scale=length_scale, 
  noise_sd = noise_sd
)
gp_reg <- gaussian_process_regression(
  X=X, y=y, X_test = X_test, 
  signal_sd=signal_sd, 
  length_scale=length_scale, 
  noise_sd = noise_sd
)
plot(gp_reg)

set.seed(rand_seed)
length_scale <- 3
signal_sd <- 1.16
noise_sd <- 0.89
y <- gaussian_process(
  X=X, 
  signal_sd=signal_sd, 
  length_scale=length_scale, 
  noise_sd = noise_sd
)
gp_reg <- gaussian_process_regression(
  X=X, y=y, X_test = X_test, 
  signal_sd=signal_sd, 
  length_scale=length_scale, 
  noise_sd = noise_sd
)
plot(gp_reg)
